title: -P-wave assignment of U-238 neutron resonances.-

x4codes.shortRef: Conf: Conf.on Nucl.Cross-Sect.and Techn.,Washington 1975, Vol.2, p.733 (1975)

x4freetext: .For measuring gammas above 4.3 and 1.5 MeV two runs
made: one with 13.9 g/cm**2 U-238 plate (0.4 %
U-235) of size 10x10 cm and inclined 45 degree to
n-beam, the second with 4.64 g/cm**2 U-238 disc
(0.2 % U-235) 12 cm diam. placed perpendicular to
Two 7 x 6 inch NaI(Tl) detectors for measuring
independence of the capture gamma-ray cascade.
.New method for determining p-wave assignment of U-238
resonances presented consisting of measuring the
fraction of capture gamma-rays above 4.3 MeV.

Re-normalization factor was applied to the data such
